														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1288060">
									

<p>yes, this. i was trying to figure what bothered me. it's definitely the bolding. those are the points you're wanting to emphasize, but this isnt written as an informational document, this is written as a story, and the bolding doesnt fit well.</p>
<p>i'm somewhat ok with the doctor vomiting when he finds out theyre responsible, but i had an issue with how that information was stated.</p>
<p>it seems that you would want it to be that the doctor asked them questions we dont hear him ask(you know what 447-2 does to dead bodies? &#8230;.you know what procedure 110-Montauk is???) to which they were answering &quot;yes&quot;, which makes him vomit at the idea</p>
<p>instead with how it's written it sounds more like he's just going on a ramble there and TRYING to sound dramatic, like he's answering unasked questions.</p>
<p>that and the bolding are the only things that stand out negative though. i love everything else about this so hard.</p>

							</div>

								
